"text\":\"**Considering git diff and untracked files**\\n\\nI'm thinking that if the initial file isn't tracked, maybe only attempts to capture tracked changes are being recorded. We operate within the worktree, and the final diff should include untracked files. However, if automation is only looking at `git diff`, untracked files might not be part of that output. Typically, a commit would include all changes, so it doesn't seem to be a significant issue.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Refining test execution**\\n\\nI need to ensure that execution within a test method triggers in the right order. JUnit doesn't guarantee that order, so I'll add `@TestMethodOrder(OrderAnnotation.class)` and `@Order(1)`. That seems better than relying on static methods. My initial thought had some doubts about whether it would guarantee order, but transitioning to an ordered approach seems valid. I'll also need to import `Order`, `TestMethodOrder`, and `MethodOrderer` to implement these changes correctly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_jcQGBkJs0Ye92OOOQKVOa7Z3|fc_0311e6f268442dbc0169f529092f08819e9c078d0e66aa605c", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/src/test/java/jspapi/jsp_api/TagSupportTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class TagSupportTest {\n    private static final Tag TAG_INTERFACE_ANCESTOR = findTagInterfaceAncestor();\n\n    @Test\n    void primesTagInterfaceLookupDuringTestClassInitialization() {\n        assertThat(TAG_INTERFACE_ANCESTOR).isInstanceOf(TagSupport.class);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void findsAncestorOfRequestedTagSupportClass() {", "newText": "import org.junit.jupiter.api.MethodOrderer;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Order;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.TestMethodOrder;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\n@TestMethodOrder(MethodOrderer.OrderAnnotation.class)\npublic class TagSupportTest {\n    @Test\n    @Order(1)\n    void primesTagInterfaceLookupThroughPublicApi() {\n        TagSupport child = new TagSupport();\n        TagSupport parent = new TagSupport();\n        child.setParent(parent);\n\n        Tag ancestor = TagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, Tag.class);\n\n        assertThat(ancestor).isSameAs(parent);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    @Order(2)\n    void findsAncestorOfRequestedTagSupportClass() {"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void findsAncestorByTagInterface() {", "newText": "    @Test\n    @Order(3)\n    void findsAncestorByTagInterface() {"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void returnsNullWhenRequestedClassIsNotATagType() {", "newText": "    @Test\n    @Order(4)\n    void returnsNullWhenRequestedClassIsNotATagType() {"}, {"oldText": "\n    private static Tag findTagInterfaceAncestor() {\n        TagSupport child = new TagSupport();\n        TagSupport parent = new TagSupport();\n        child.setParent(parent);\n\n        return TagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, Tag.class);\n    }\n", "newText": "\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 740, "output": 2150, "cacheRead": 47104, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 49994, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777674478185, "responseId": "resp_0311e6f268442dbc0169f528eec4a0819eb9fdbd86971e4040"}}
